Vishing (Voice-based) – Theory
What is Vishing?

Vishing uses phone calls instead of emails.

Examples

Fake bank calls

Fake tech support

Fake HR calls

Red Flags

Asking for OTP or PIN

Threats or urgency

Caller ID spoofing


Smishing (SMS-based) – Theory
What is Smishing?

Smishing is phishing via SMS messages.

Examples

Fake delivery messages

Fake prize winnings

Fake KYC updates

Defense

Don’t click unknown links

Verify sender

Use spam filters

 OSINT (Passive & Legal)
 OSINT Rules

No login bypass

No hacking

Only publicly available data
No login bypass

No hacking

Only publicly available data
